What is Sysmon?

Sysmon (System Monitor) is part of Microsoft Sysinternals.

It extends Windows logging dramatically.

Default Windows logs are limited.

Sysmon provides:

Process Creation
Network Connections
Registry Changes
DNS Queries
File Activity
Process Injection Detection
Why Sysmon is Important

Without Sysmon:

User Logged In
Process Started

Limited information.

With Sysmon:

Process Name
Parent Process
PID
Command Line
Hash
User
Network Activity

Full visibility.

